defaultEqually important is combating confirmation bias—the tendency of authors to place too much weight on their own views relative to other views [
defaultcitation
default]
default.
default As pointed out to the Committe
defaulte by a presenter and some questionnaire respondents, alternative views are not always cited in a chapter if the Lead Authors do not agree with them. Getting the balance right is an ongoing struggle.
